// =============================================================================
// oracle-mcp — MCP server registration block (TEMPLATE / single source)
// =============================================================================
// This is the canonical "oracle" entry for the `mcp` object of a Kilo Code
// (~/.config/kilo/kilo.jsonc) or Claude Code MCP config. It is used three ways:
//
//   * ORACLE_MCP_CLIENT=kilo   -> the setup script inserts the block (below,
//                                 including its // markers) as the FIRST child
//                                 of the existing `mcp` object, idempotently,
//                                 and removes it again on cleanup. No jq — the
//                                 surrounding comments and key order survive.
//   * ORACLE_MCP_CLIENT=print  -> the block is printed for manual paste.
//   * ORACLE_MCP_CLIENT=claude -> ignored; the script uses `claude mcp add`.
//
// The `//>>> oracle-mcp:managed` / `//<<< oracle-mcp:managed` markers are the
// idempotency anchor: install skips if present, cleanup deletes between them.
// Do NOT remove or rename the markers by hand — run `setup.sh cleanup` instead.
//
// The server exposes ALL of SQLcl's saved connections (e.g. "{{ORACLE_CONN_NAME}}");
// no credentials appear here — they live in SQLcl's secure store.
// =============================================================================
//>>> oracle-mcp:managed (oracle-mcp skill) — remove via: setup.sh|ps1 cleanup >>>
"oracle": {
  "type": "local",
  "command": ["sql", "-mcp"]
},
//<<< oracle-mcp:managed <<<
